com.mmm.cms.homehealth.proto

Interface DiagnosisCodeIF

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, CodePositionalIF, CodeUlcerIF, java.lang.Comparable, Describable, EtiologyPairingIF, OptionalPaymentCodeIF, PrimaryAwardableIF
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDiagnosisCode, DiagnosisCode, DiagnosisCode_Empty

    public interface DiagnosisCodeIF
extends Describable, CodePositionalIF, CodeUlcerIF, PrimaryAwardableIF, OptionalPaymentCodeIF, EtiologyPairingIF, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable
    Holds the information specific to the ICD-9 Diagnosis codes (as opposed to a procedure code) that supports Home Health scoring. Dec 2010 - 3M - Refactored this class to allow method definitions to be more ala carte for the transition to I-10 coding.
    Author:
    3M Health Information Systems for CMS Home Health
